					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Jo Scott-Coe</h4>
												<p>Jo Scott-Coe is the author of three nonfiction books: <em>Teacher at Point Blank</em>, <em>MASS: A Sniper, a Father, and a Priest</em>, and most recently, <em>Unheard Witness</em>. Her articles have appeared in <em>TIME</em>, <em>Catapult</em>, <em>Salon</em>, <em>Tahoma Literary Review</em>, <em>American Studies Journal</em>, and many other publications. She is Professor of English at Riverside City College and also teaches community writing workshops with the Inlandia Institute.</p>
